      • runTimeInsert

        public java.lang.String runTimeInsert(int numberOfTimes,
                                      int seed)
        This method returns a String containing all times taken to insert a certain number of elements into a hash table.
        Parameters:
        numberOfTimes - The number of times we should increment the number of items added to the hash table. Each increment has a step size of 1000000.
        seed - The seed used for pseudorandom number generation.
        Returns:
        String A String containing all times in ns taken to complete this operation. Put in a form conducive to .csv files.

      • runTimeFind

        public java.lang.String runTimeFind(int numberOfTimes,
                                    int seed,
                                    boolean valid)
        This method returns a String corresponding to the time taken to find a certain key in a hash table.
        Parameters:
        numberOfTimes - The number of times we should increment the number of items added to the hash table. Each increment has a step size of 1000000.
        seed - The seed used for pseudorandom number generation.
        valid - A boolean representing whether we want a valid number or not. If true then we insert a unique key, and then we insert the number of elements -1, and then search for the valid, unique, key. If false then we add positive numbers and search for a negative number.
        Returns:
        String The times taken in ns to complete this operation, in a format conducive to .csv files.

        seed - The seed used for pseudorandom number generation.
        Returns:
        String The max number of elements at an index in the hash table, in a format conducive to .csv files.
